soldier settler
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:1. a new settler enticed to New Zealand as soldier in the 1860s by the promise of land. 2. a returned serviceman who became a farmer following war service.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:returned man; rehab farmer
Pronunciation:
Notes:
